xxl.applications.pipes.traffic
Class Highway

java.lang.Object
  xxl.applications.pipes.traffic.Highway

public class Highway
extends Object

This class contains methods to connect some real data from a highway to xxl (http://www.clearingstelle-verkehr.de/cs/verkehrsdaten/katalog/katalogberichte/fsp/fsp_metadaten). The data can be used in xxl as source with the getSourceByDate() methods or as cursor with the getCursorBydate() methods.
Before using the source methods, the original data have to be transformed with the the makeAllSourceFiles method, that divide the large files to several small. the format of the generated files is as follows:
" time(long) \t distance to Marina(int) \t laneNumber(byte) \t speed(double) \t length(double) \t direction" the time is measured in ms after January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 GMT. (The original data format : distance to Marina, laneNumber, time, speed, length) The cursor methods allow the use of both data by selecting the appropriate Converter.
Important: The original files need to be converted. Use Highway.makeAllSourcesFiles(, ); to do that or start the main method of Highway with the corresponding two arguments.

computeValues

protected static void computeValues(String inputFileName)
Computes basisDate, direction and a outputFileName of a highway file. the outputname depends on the given file inputFileName. example: If the inputFile is "lp021693_N_speeds_and_lengths.dat" the names of the generated files are 16-02-1993-N-81840-lane_0 (where 81840 is the distance to the city marina).

Parameters:
inputFileName - ther name of the input file.

getSourceByDate

public static HighwaySource getSourceByDate(String path,
                                            Date from,
                                            Date to,
                                            char direction,
                                            int distanceToCity,
                                            short lane,
                                            float factor)
Returns a source, that matches the given date, the given direction and the given distance to the city marina in the given directory.

Parameters:
path - the directory, where generated files are stored
from - the startdate including the startdate.
to - the enddate excluding the enddate.
direction - the direction possible values are 'N' for north, 'S' for south or ' ' for both
distanceToCity - the distance to the city marina. if a value less than 1 is given, this parameter will be ignored.
lane - the selected lane number. If a value less than 0 is given, this parameter will be ignored.
factor - a factor to speed up or slow down the original tupel rate. for instance 0,5 will increase the speed by 100%, 2 decrease the speed to 50% of the original rate.
Returns:
HighwaySource

makeSourceFile

protected static void makeSourceFile(String fileName,
                                     String path)
Produces a source file that can be used by getsourcebydate and getcursorbydate methods. to create one source that delivers tuples in the same way as the highway sensors. Invalid measuring is ignored.

Parameters:
fileName - the original file from "http://www.clearingstelle-verkehr.de/cs/verkehrsdaten/katalog/katalogberichte/fsp/fsp_metadaten" that will be proceeded.
path - the path to the file.

splitHighwayFile

protected static void splitHighwayFile(String fullQualifiedFileName,
                                       String tempDir)
Splits a File with highway data to several small temp files. Every temp file contains the data of one source. the temp filenames are saved in fileList.

Parameters:
fullQualifiedFileName - a string containing the absolute path and the filename. of the highway data, that will be split.
tempDir - the directory where the tmpfiles should be stored. if tempDir doesn't exist it will be created
